ontal rule separators aren't functioning as headings.\n\nLooking at the class names and standard Java types in the source, they're either present in the knowledge file or acceptable to omit as standard library classes. The more interesting finding is that the hint \"固定長可変長\" actually does have a basis—it comes from a commented-out RST block mentioning support for both fixed and variable-length data formats, so it's not fabricated, just sourced from non-rendered content.\n\nThe real issue I'm identifying is the translation of the RST `note` directive as \"注意\" (caution/warning) when it should convey neutral informational context instead. That's the only substantive discrepancy worth noting.\n\nI'm also checking whether the figure reference and its explanatory text made it into the knowledge file properly. The source mentions a diagram showing the three-element structure, and while the figure itself can't be included in JSON, the accompanying explanation appears to be captured adequately in the knowledge file's description of the three components.\n\nSo I'll note just that one minor issue about the note/注意 labeling inconsistency and call this review complete.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":20089,"cache_read_input_tokens":29873,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":20089,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7b717065-65a5-4630-8bcc-f794456d275b","uuid":"0bd922ae-acf9-4cf1-957e-5fa0d3648780"}
